column2:
QD70D not prepared
Start was made when the QD70D was not ready.
column3: After switching power from OFF to ON/resetting the PLC CPU, turn ON the PLC READY signal (Yn0) again, make sure that the module READY signal (Xn0) is ON, and then make a start. (The module is faulty if the module READY signal (Xn0) does not turn ON.)

At start:
Perform JOG operation to change 'Current feed value' to within the software stroke limit range.
Current value changing:
Change the new current value to within the software stroke limit range.
During operation:
Correct 'Positioning address/movement amount'.
